    {
        "id": "628495559e4fdb50",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "2c5dc8e60bfa2009",
        "name": "Delta DVP12SE addressing (IMPORTANT)",
        "info": "Node-RED (node-red-contrib-modbus) uses 0-based addresses.\n\nM bits:\n- M0 = 2048\n- M1 = 2049  (stopReady)\n- M2 = 2050  (stopAck)\n\nD registers:\n- D0 = 4096\n- D10 = 4106\n\nIf you used the 1-based Modbus table (M0=2049), subtract 1 for Node-RED.",
        "x": 270,
        "y": 40,
        "wires": []
    },
